===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|lynspin}}, compound of {{m|enm|lins|t=axletree}} and {{m|enm|pin}}, from {{der|en|ang|lynis|t=linchpin}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*luniso}} (compare {{cog|de|Lünse}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|-}} (compare {{cog|cy|olwyn|t=wheel}}, {{cog|xcl|ողն|t=back; spine, backbone}}, {{cog|sa|आणि|t=linchpin|tr=āṇí}}). Figurative use attested from the mid-20th century.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A pin inserted through holes at the end of an [[axle]], so as to secure a wheel.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A central [[cohesive]] source of [[stability]] and [[security]]; a person or thing that is critical to a system or organisation.

